# Ignore python virtual environment
# NOTE: beginning from python 3.13, venv creates its own .gitignore that ignores
#   everything in venv/. This has the side effect that ripgrep stops working
#   when called inside the venv/ which differs from venv/ being excluded when
#   called in a directory above it (Use-case: inspecting the code of an
#   installed module). To prevent the creation the venv should be created with
#   `--without-scm-ignore-files`.
venv/

